Visualization:
   Process of representing the data in the form graph or flow chart

In python Visualization can be achieved by four different libraries :

1.matplotlib
2.seaborn
3.plotly
4.dash

Installation:

pip install matplotlib
pip install seaborn


External tool for visualization : Power BI and Tableau

Focus : Power BI

Visualization :

1.matplotlib can works on its own
2.seaborn is built on to of matplotlib so when we use seaborn
we need to use both seaborn and matplotlib

Visualization Types:

1.Uni-Variate ---> Only with one input
2.Bi-Variate ---> With two input (x and y)

Dimension : We will focussing on only two dimensional images

Visualization :

1.number vs number (x numeric and y numeric)
2.number vs category (x category and y numeric)
3.number only (uni-Variate)

